# Session Knowledge Artifact

Every agent session that changes code, makes a decision, or produces analysis
must leave a structured `SessionArtifact v1` behind so it becomes part of the
company brain (repo -> project -> department -> company knowledge ladder).
Canonical policy: `config/governance-contract.yaml` (`external_integrations`).
Wire contract: `POST $VMC_BASE_URL/api/vmc/knowledge/session-artifact` (e.g.
`https://missioncontrol.tayloralton.com`), schema owned by the agentic-swarm
repo (`apps/vmc-web/src/lib/vmc/knowledge/session-artifact.ts`). Artifacts
from this repo are tagged `repo: "PLX_MC"`.

## When this applies

- Code changed, a decision was made, a lesson was learned, or non-trivial
  research/investigation happened.
- **Exempt:** trivial read-only Q&A sessions with no code change, no decision,
  and nothing worth remembering later.

## How capture happens (do not duplicate work the hook already does)

- **Cursor** `sessionEnd` hook (`scripts/compliance-closeout.mjs`) captures
  this automatically — best-effort assembly from git state (branch, status)
  plus a POST to the VMC ingestion endpoint. If the hook is configured and
  ran, do nothing extra.
- **Runtimes without hook support**, or a session you know ran without the
  hook firing (e.g. a detached worktree, a manual/background session), submit
  manually using the `session-brain` skill from the agentic-swarm repo
  (`.cursor/skills/session-brain`) — same schema, same endpoint, `repo:
  "PLX_MC"`.
- If unsure whether the hook fired, submit manually anyway — duplicate
  artifacts are harmless; a missing artifact is not.

## Fail-open, always

- Capture must **never block or fail a session**. `compliance-closeout.mjs`
  always exits 0 regardless of ingestion outcome.
- If `VMC_API_KEY` is missing, VMC is unreachable, or the POST fails, the
  hook writes the same JSON body to the local offline queue instead of
  losing it: `artifacts/session-brain/<yyyy-mm-dd>/<session_id>.json`. Do
  not retry indefinitely or hold up the session waiting on the network.
- Kill switch: `SESSION_BRAIN_ENABLED=0` disables capture entirely (the hook
  exits 0 immediately) — respect it, do not work around it.

## Ladder tagging

- Tag every artifact with `repo: "PLX_MC"`, and where applicable
  `project_slug`, so memory-graph rollups can group sessions by repo and
  project on the way up to the company-wide view.
